    <p>Health­ier Liv­ing</p>
    <p>Un­der­stand stress bet­ter in the age of the coronaviru­s.</p>
    <p>The World Health Or­gan­i­sa­tion has called for mas­sive scal­ing up of men­tal health in­vest­ment. Glob­ally, close to one bil­lion peo­ple are liv­ing with a men­tal dis­or­der, and one per­son dies every 40 sec­onds by sui­cide. The Straits Times' se­nior health cor­re­spon­dent Joyce Teo hosts Dr Jared Ng, a con­sul­tant with emer­gency ser­vices at the In­sti­tute of Men­tal Health. He talks about the re­cent cases he has seen. Find out more by scan­ning this episode us­ing our QR code. str.sg/JWaN</p>

